    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="555"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115C96/60</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Querétaro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 19, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The text has been furnished me of decree declaring that on account of connection
                    with the Santa Ysabel massacre<note n="2" xml:id="d555fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">See</hi> Protection of Americans and American interests,
                            <ref target="#pg_653">p. 653</ref>.</note> Francisco Villa, Rafael
                    Castro and Pablo Lopez are outside the law, and that any citizen may apprehend
                    and execute them, the only formality being their identification.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
